<!-- ABOUT LIGHTNING -->
<article class="content-card">
  <h2>About Lightning</h2>
  <p>
    Lightning is a powerful natural electrical discharge caused by imbalances between storm clouds and the ground.
    It can strike people, trees, buildings, and electrical systems, making thunderstorms extremely dangerous.
  </p>
  <p>
    India records thousands of lightning strikes every year, especially in Jharkhand, Odisha, UP, West Bengal, Bihar, and Northeast states.
  </p>
</article>

<!-- WARNING SIGNS -->
<article class="content-card">
  <h2>Warning Signs of a Thunderstorm</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Dark, towering clouds forming rapidly.</li>
    <li>Strong winds and sudden temperature drop.</li>
    <li>Continuous thunder or distant rumbles.</li>
    <li>Frequent lightning flashes.</li>
  </ul>
</article>

<!-- IMD ALERTS -->
