    <li><strong>Orange Alert:</strong> Be prepared ‚Äî lightning expected.</li>
    <li><strong>Red Alert:</strong> Take action ‚Äî severe thunderstorms and lightning.</li>
  </ul>
</article>

<!-- OUTDOOR SAFETY -->
<article class="content-card">
  <h2>Outdoor Safety Measures</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Immediately move indoors or into a car.</li>
    <li>Avoid open fields, hilltops, and water bodies.</li>
    <li>Do NOT stand under trees or electric poles.</li>
    <li>Do NOT use umbrellas with metal tips.</li>
    <li>Stay away from bikes, cycles, and metal objects.</li>
  </ul>
</article>

<!-- INDOOR SAFETY -->
<article class="content-card">
  <h2>Indoor Safety Measures</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Stay away from windows and doors.</li>
    <li>Do NOT use wired phones or wired electronics.</li>
    <li>Avoid touching metal faucets or water taps.</li>
    <li>Turn off and unplug appliances.</li>
    <li>Do NOT bathe or shower during lightning.</li>
  </ul>
</article>

<!-- FIRST AID -->
<article class="content-card">
  <h2>First Aid for Lightning Victims</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Call emergency services immediately.</li>
    <li>Check breathing ‚Äî give CPR if unresponsive.</li>
    <li>Move the person to a safe, dry place.</li>
    <li>Cover them with a cloth to prevent hypothermia.</li>
    <li>Lightning victims do NOT carry electricity ‚Äî safe to touch.</li>
  </ul>
</article>

